Legion of Super-Heroes v3 #13
Publisher:  DC Comics
Publication Date:  August 1985

Writers:  Paul Levitz
Pencillers:  Steve Lightle
Inkers:  Larry Mahlstedt
Colorists:  Carl Gafford
Letterer:  John Costanza
Cover:  Steve Lightle, Larry Mahlstedt, and Anthony Tollin

Timber Wolf and Karate Kid's Sensei travel to the planet Lythlys to carry out the last will of Karate Kid. Along the way, they meet a young man named Myg whom the Sensei senses could train to be a hero, much like the Karate Kid. It is revealed that Karate Kid wanted Timber Wolf to plant a seed within the rocks of the rough terrain of Lythlys, completing a legend that if a plant grows on the planet, the planet would grow weak. Since that was the planet that Karate Kid's biological father, Black Dragon, turned to crime, it was important to him. Meanwhile, applicants arrive to try to join the Legion of Super-Heroes. 

